=== Cilia and Flagella Structure
- "9 + 2" arrangement of microtubules in the *axoneme*.
- *Kinetosome* (basal body) at the base consists of nine triplets of microtubules (similar to centrioles).
- *Sliding microtubule hypothesis*: Movement powered by ATP and dynein arms causing microtubules to slide past each other.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-9").path, width: 60%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-9").caption
)
- Structure of a flagellum showing the axoneme (9 pairs + 2 central microtubules) and kinetosome.

=== Pseudopodia Mechanism
- Cytoplasm divided into *ectoplasm* (gel state) and *endoplasm* (sol state).
- Movement involves actin subunits, actin-binding proteins (ABPs), and myosin.
- Hydrostatic force forces endoplasm into the *hyaline cap*.
- Actin polymerizes to form gel-like ectoplasm (tube).
- Contraction at the trailing edge (myosin + actin) forces fluid endoplasm forward.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-10").path, width: 60%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-10").caption
)
- Diagram of ameboid movement showing endoplasm streaming into the hyaline cap and conversion to ectoplasm.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-11").path, width: 60%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-11").caption
)
- Cross-section of an axopodium showing the spiral array of microtubules.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-12").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-12").caption
)
- Molecular mechanism of pseudopodial movement involving actin polymerization and myosin interaction.

== Functional Components of Protozoan Cells
- *Nucleus*: Membrane-bound, often vesicular. Ciliates have *macronuclei* (compact) and *micronuclei*.
- *Mitochondria*: Energy production. Cristae shape (flat, tubular, discoid, branched) is a taxonomic character.
    - *Hydrogenosomes*: Function in absence of oxygen (mitochondrial derivatives).
    - *Kinetoplasts*: Mitochondrial derivatives with DNA disc.
- *Golgi Apparatus* (dictyosomes): Secretory system. *Parabasal bodies* are similar.
- *Plastids*: Contain photosynthetic pigments (chloroplasts).
- *Extrusomes*: Membrane-bound organelles for extrusion (e.g., *trichocysts*).

