== Excretion and Osmoregulation
- *Contractile vacuoles*: Function in osmoregulation (removing excess water).
- Common in freshwater forms; rare in marine/parasitic forms.
- Mechanism: Proton pumps transport #ce("H^+") and #ce("HCO_3^-") into vacuole, drawing water in by osmosis.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-15").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-15").caption
)
- Contractile vacuole of *Paramecium* with feeder canals and ampullae.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-16").path, width: 60%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-16").caption
)
- Proposed mechanism: Proton pumps create osmotic gradient to fill vacuole; contents expelled to outside.

== Reproduction
- Asexual:
    - *Binary fission*: Two identical individuals.
    - *Budding*: Progeny smaller than parent.
    - *Multiple fission* (schizogony): Several nuclear divisions precede cytokinesis.
- Sexual:
    - *Syngamy*: Fusion of gametes (isogametes or anisogametes).
    - *Conjugation*: Exchange of gametic nuclei between paired organisms.
    - *Autogamy*: Self-fertilization.
- *Encystment*: Formation of dormant *cysts* with resistant coverings to survive harsh conditions.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-17").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-17").caption
)
- Binary fission in *Arcella*, *Euglypha*, *Trypanosoma*, and *Euglena*.

= MAJOR PROTOZOAN TAXA

== Opisthokonta
- Flattened mitochondrial cristae; one posterior flagellum.
- Includes metazoans, fungi, *choanoflagellates*, and microsporidians.
- *Choanoflagellates*: Solitary or colonial; likely sister taxon to metazoans.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-18").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-18").caption
)
- Relationship of choanoflagellates (*Codonosiga*, *Proterospongia*) to Metazoa.

== Stramenopiles
- Tubular mitochondrial cristae; heterokont flagellates (two different flagella: one hairy, one smooth).
- Includes brown algae, yellow algae, diatoms, opalinids, and some heliozoans.

== Viridiplantae
- Green algae and plants; chloroplasts with chlorophylls *a* and *b*.
- *Phylum Chlorophyta*:
    - *Chlamydomonas*: Single-celled.
    - *Gonium*, *Pandorina*, *Eudorina*: Colonial.
    - *Volvox*: Hollow sphere of thousands of cells; division of labor (somatic vs. reproductive cells).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-19").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-19").caption
)
- Examples of Chlorophyta: *Chlamydomonas*, *Gonium*, *Eudorina*, *Pandorina*.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-20").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-20").caption
)
- Life cycle of *Volvox* showing asexual (daughter colonies) and sexual reproduction.

== Euglenozoa
- Discoid mitochondrial cristae; longitudinal microtubules beneath cell membrane (*pellicle*).
- *Subphylum Euglenida*:
    - Chloroplasts with chlorophyll *b* (secondary endosymbiosis).
    - *Euglena*: Flagellum, reservoir, stigma (eyespot), paramylon granules (starchlike storage).
    - Nutrition: Autotrophic or saprozoic (if in dark).
- *Subphylum Kinetoplasta*:
    - *Kinetoplast*: Modified mitochondrion with DNA disc.
    - Parasitic.
    - *Trypanosoma*: Causes African sleeping sickness (*T. brucei*, vector: tsetse fly) and Chagas' disease (*T. cruzi*, vector: kissing bug).
    - *Leishmania*: Causes visceral, cutaneous, or mucocutaneous diseases (vector: sand flies).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-21").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-21").caption
)
- *Peranema*, *Phacus*, *Trypanosoma*, and *Leishmania*.

== Retortamonada and Diplomonads
- Lack mitochondria (secondary loss).
- *Diplomonads*: *Giardia lamblia* (intestinal parasite causing diarrhea).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-22").path, width: 40%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-22").caption
)
- *Giardia lamblia*.

== Alveolata
- Shared presence of *alveoli* (membrane-bound sacs beneath cell membrane).
- Includes Ciliophora, Dinoflagellata, and Apicomplexa.

=== Phylum Ciliophora
- Body covered with *cilia*.
- Multinucleate: *Macronucleus* (metabolic/developmental) and *Micronucleus* (sexual).
- *Pellicle* armor; *infraciliature* (kinetosomes + fibrils).
- *Trichocysts* and *toxicysts* (defensive extrusomes).
- *Cytostome* (mouth) and *cytoproct* (waste expulsion).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-23").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-23").caption
)
- Representative ciliates: *Euplotes*, *Tetrahymena*, *Dileptus*, *Stentor*, *Vorticella*.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-24").path, width: 60%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-24").caption
)
- Infraciliature and trichocysts.

- *Suctorians*: Young are ciliated/free-swimming; adults are sessile with tentacles for feeding (*Podophrya*).
- *Symbiotic Ciliates*: *Balantidium coli* (parasitic in humans), *Ichthyophthirius* ("ick" in fish), *Entodinium* (ruminants).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-25").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-25").caption
)
- *Ichthyophthirius*, *Entodinium*, *Balantidium coli*.

- *Paramecium*:
    - Slipper-shaped; oral groove; pellicle; cytostome; cytopharynx; contractile vacuoles.
    - Holozoic feeder (bacteria, algae).
    - Movement: Spiral path; *avoiding reaction* (reverses cilia upon stimulus).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-26").path, width: 60%),
