=== Phylum Dinoflagellata
- Two flagella (equatorial and longitudinal) in grooves.
- Many photoautotrophic; important primary producers (zooxanthellae in corals).
- Some produce "red tides" and toxins (*Pfiesteria*, *Ciguatera*).
- *Noctiluca*: Bioluminescent, voracious predator.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-29").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-29").caption
)
- *Ceratium*, *Noctiluca*, *Gymnodinium*.

=== Phylum Apicomplexa
- Endoparasites; *Apical complex* (rhoptries, micronemes, etc.) for penetrating host.
- Life cycle: Asexual (schizogony) and sexual (sporogony); *spore* (oocyst).
- *Class Coccidea*:
    - *Eimeria*: Coccidiosis in fowl.
    - *Toxoplasma gondii*: Toxoplasmosis (cats are definitive hosts); dangerous for pregnant women and AIDS patients.
    - *Plasmodium*: Malaria (Vector: *Anopheles* mosquito).
        - *P. falciparum* (most virulent), *P. vivax*, *P. malariae*, *P. ovale*.
        - Life cycle: Sporozoites injected -> Liver (schizogony) -> Merozoites -> Red blood cells (trophozoites -> schizogony) -> Gametocytes -> Mosquito (sexual cycle -> sporozoites).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-30").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-30").caption
)
- Apical complex structure and *Eimeria* oocyst.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-31").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-31").caption
)
- Life cycle of *Plasmodium vivax*.

== Parabasalids
- *Axostyle* (stiffening rod of microtubules).
- *Parabasal body* (modified Golgi).
- *Trichomonas vaginalis*: Causes vaginitis (sexually transmitted).
- Symbionts in termites (*Trichonympha*).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-32").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-32").caption
)
- *Trichomonas*, *Trichonympha*, *Spirotrichonympha*.

== Amebas
- Polyphyletic group.
- *Nonactinopod Amebas*:
    - *Rhizopodans*: Lobopodia, filopodia, or rhizopodia.
    - *Amoeba proteus*: Freshwater, lobopodia.
    - *Heterolobosea*: *Naegleria fowleri* (amebic meningitis).
    - *Entamoebidae*: *Entamoeba histolytica* (amebic dysentery).
- *Granuloreticulosa*:
    - *Foraminiferans*: Reticulopodia; calcium carbonate tests (many chambered).
    - Important fossils; form limestone/chalk deposits (White Cliffs of Dover).

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-33").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-33").caption
)
- Foraminiferan with reticulopodia and test.

- *Actinopod Amebas*:
    - *Heliozoans*: Freshwater, axopodia (*Actinosphaerium*).
    - *Radiolarians*: Marine, siliceous skeletons, central capsule. Oldest known protozoa.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-11-34").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-11-34").caption
)
- Radiolarian tests.

= PHYLOGENY AND ADAPTIVE DIVERSIFICATION
- Molecular evidence suggests eukaryotic diversification into supergroups (Chromalveolates, Unikonts, Plantae, Rhizaria, Excavates).
